5000|$|Malaviya {{became the}} President of the Indian National Congress in 1909 and 1918. He was a {{moderate}} leader and opposed the <b>separate</b> <b>electorates</b> for Muslims under the Lucknow Pact of 1916. The [...] "Mahamana" [...] title was conferred {{to him by}} Rabindranath Tagore.|$|R
