50|$|Nawab M. Ismail Khan entered {{politics}} {{at a very}} early age. As a young man, he had closely observed the agitation of the Muslims masses for a <b>separate</b> <b>electorate</b> and had seen how a delegation of the Muslims was sent (October 1906) to Lord Minto -- which secured the right of a separate representation for the Muslims.|$|E
