50|$|The Rev Frank Isitt was {{nominated}} as the Prohibitionist candidate for ten <b>separate</b> <b>electorates,</b> and came second in eight. Another candidate, D Whyte, {{was nominated}} for two. Both men stood {{to ensure that a}} local liquor licensing poll was held in each electorate for which they were nominated.|$|R
